## Enqueuing Jobs

### Immediate Execution

```ruby
# Enqueue job to run ASAP
ArticleNotificationJob.perform_later(@article.id)

# In controller
def create
  @article = Current.user.articles.build(article_params)
  
  if @article.save
    ArticleNotificationJob.perform_later(@article.id)
    redirect_to @article, notice: "Article created."
  else
    render :new, status: :unprocessable_entity
  end
end
```

### Delayed Execution

```ruby
# Enqueue with delay
ArticleNotificationJob.set(wait: 1.hour).perform_later(@article.id)

# Enqueue at specific time
ArticleNotificationJob.set(wait_until: Date.tomorrow.noon).perform_later(@article.id)

# Enqueue at specific datetime
publish_time = Time.zone.parse("2025-12-25 09:00:00")
ArticleNotificationJob.set(wait_until: publish_time).perform_later(@article.id)
```

### Priority

```ruby
# Higher number = higher priority
ArticleNotificationJob.set(priority: 10).perform_later(@article.id)

# Low priority (background cleanup)
CleanupJob.set(priority: -10).perform_later

# Default priority is 0
```

### Custom Queue

```ruby
# Enqueue to specific queue
ArticleNotificationJob.set(queue: :high_priority).perform_later(@article.id)

# Configure in job class
class UrgentNotificationJob < ApplicationJob
  queue_as :urgent
  
  def perform(user_id)
    # Handle urgent notification
  end
end
```

